_🧹 Nitpick_ | _🔵 Trivial_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Avoid cloning the full batch on every flush — use `drain(..)`.**

`batch.iter().cloned().zip(claimed)` deep-copies every `LogBatchEntry` (each has many `String` fields including `raw`, `message`, `ai_*`) at flush time, even though `batch` is immediately cleared after the loop. With chunks up to `MAX_INDEX_CHUNK_RECORDS = 500` and `MAX_INDEX_CHUNK_BYTES = 4 MiB`, this is a needless allocation churn per flush.




<details>
<summary>♻️ Move entries instead of cloning</summary>

```diff
-    let claimed = checkpoint::claim_imports_in_tx(&tx, source_id, imports)?;
-    let mut claimed_batch = Vec::with_capacity(batch.len());
-    let mut skipped_dupes = 0usize;
-    for (entry, claimed) in batch.iter().cloned().zip(claimed) {
-        if claimed {
-            claimed_batch.push(entry);
-        } else {
-            skipped_dupes += 1;
-        }
-    }
+    let claimed = checkpoint::claim_imports_in_tx(&tx, source_id, imports)?;
+    let mut claimed_batch = Vec::with_capacity(batch.len());
+    let mut skipped_dupes = 0usize;
+    for (entry, was_claimed) in batch.drain(..).zip(claimed) {
+        if was_claimed {
+            claimed_batch.push(entry);
+        } else {
+            skipped_dupes += 1;
+        }
+    }
@@
-    batch.clear();
     imports.clear();
```

Note: `drain(..)` empties `batch` even on partial iteration, so the explicit `batch.clear()` becomes redundant.

</details>

